132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1637
S.P. 645 In Senate, April 15, 2025
An Act to Reform the Midcoast Regional Redevelopment Authority
Received by the Secretary of the Senate on April 11, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Housing and Economic Development pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by President DAUGHTRY of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Representative ANKELES of Brunswick and
Senator: TEPLER of Sagadahoc, Representatives: ARFORD of Brunswick, GOLEK of
Harpswell.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §13083-G, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 641, §1, is amended
3 to read:
4 2. Intermediate goal. Recover economic losses and total job losses in the primary
5 impact community resulting from the base closure; and
6 Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §13083-G, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 641, §1, is amended
7 to read:
8 3. Long-term goal. Facilitate the maximum redevelopment of base properties.; and
9 Sec. 3. 5 MRSA §13083-G, sub-§4 is enacted to read:
10 4. Environmental stewardship. Engage in environmental stewardship to protect
11 against harm to the environment and residents of the primary impact community.
12 Sec. 4. 5 MRSA §13083-I, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 599, §1, is amended
13 to read:
14 2. Membership; appointment. The authority is governed by a board of trustees
15 composed of 11 12 voting members appointed by the Governor and subject to review by
16 the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over economic
17 development matters and to confirmation by the Senate and 2 other members, one voting
18 and one nonvoting, all appointed pursuant to this subsection.
19 A. Trustees Except for the trustees appointed pursuant to paragraphs F and G, trustees
20 are appointed for 4-year terms, except that, for initial appointments, 3 trustees are
21 appointed to one-year terms, 3 trustees are appointed to 2-year terms, 2 trustees are
22 appointed to 3-year terms, 2 trustees are appointed to 4-year terms and the
23 commissioner commissioners designated pursuant to paragraph D serves serve at the
24 pleasure of the Governor. A vacancy must be filled in the same manner as the original
25 appointment for the balance of the unexpired term.
26 B. A trustee continues to hold office until a successor is appointed and qualified, but
27 the term of the successor is not altered from the original expiration date of the holdover
28 trustee's term.
29 C. The Governor shall make 10 appointments, of which no fewer than 7 must be from
30 candidates who are residents of Androscoggin County, Cumberland County and
31 Sagadahoc County and are nominated by the primary impact communities at least 4
32 are residents of Brunswick or Brunswick town officials or business owners. The
33 Governor shall appoint members who reflect the diversity of interests represented by
34 these communities that community.
35 D. The Governor shall designate a commissioner 2 commissioners of a department 2
36 different departments of State Government to be a voting, ex officio member members
37 of the board of trustees.
38 E. A member appointed to the board of trustees may not hold an elected office in
39 municipal, county or state government.
40 F. One trustee, who serves as a voting member, must be appointed annually by the
41 chair of the Brunswick town council.
